// KNOWN BUG: `import module.symbol as alias;` parses successfully and
// passes semantic analysis (the alias is recorded on the IMPORT_STATEMENT
// node's `alias` field -- see firescript/parser/declarations.py's
// `_parse_optional_alias()` / `_parse_import()`), but nothing downstream
// actually renames the imported symbol to its alias: ast_to_fir.py /
// flir/lowering.py still look up the call by its *original* name, so any
// call site using the alias fails at FLIR lowering with
// "call to unknown function <alias>" (a LoweringError, not a normal
// diagnostic). Move this file back to tests/sources/imports/ (and generate
// the EXPECT block with `--update`) once the alias is actually threaded
// through import resolution / symbol registration so a call under the
// alias resolves to the original definition.
import @firescript/std.io.println as show;

show(5);
